  Affymetrix, Inc., (Nasdaq: AFFX) today announced that due to low initial-production yields of its most advanced commercial product, the 500K Mapping Array Set, shipment volumes have been constrained. Based on preliminary financial data, the Company expects that for the third quarter ending September 30, 2005, its product and product related revenue will be $10 -12 million below previous guidance.
Santa Clara, Calif.
Sept. 27, 2005
"During the third quarter, we experienced unusually low manufacturing yields on our new 500K Mapping Array Set." stated Stephen P.A. Fodor, Ph.D. Founder, Chairman and CEO of Affymetrix. "While we have recently seen improving yields, these improvements occurred late in the quarter and we now project that we will be unable to manufacture enough product to meet our revenue target."
